## Builder Report: S08 prb-plugin Test Harness

**Status:** PASS  
**Cycles used:** 3 / 6  
**Final phase reached:** Full gate  
**Tests:** 964 passing / 0 failing / 1 skipped (workspace-wide)  
**WIP commits:** 1 (commit hash: b5e8c6d)

### What was built

- `crates/prb-plugin-api/tests/types_test.rs`: Comprehensive tests for PluginMetadata, TransportLayer, DecodeCtx, DetectContext, WasmDecodeRequest serialization
- `crates/prb-plugin-api/tests/dto_test.rs`: Tests for CorrelationKeyDto and DebugEventDto with all field combinations
- `crates/prb-plugin-api/tests/native_test.rs`: Tests for ByteBuffer, OwnedBuffer, DetectResultFfi, and PluginDecoder trait
- `crates/prb-plugin-native/src/adapter.rs`: Added 19 comprehensive tests for dto_to_debug_event conversion covering all transports, directions, payloads, correlation keys, metadata, warnings, and addresses
- `crates/prb-plugin-wasm/src/adapter.rs`: Added 17 comprehensive tests for convert_decode_context and convert_dto_to_event functions covering all conversion scenarios
- `crates/prb-plugin-wasm/src/adapter.rs` [fix]: Added default empty payload when neither raw nor decoded payload is present (matches native adapter behavior)
- `crates/prb-plugin-wasm/src/runtime.rs`: Added 5 tests for WasmLimits default, detection, decoding, clone, and custom configurations

### Test results

| Test Package | Tests Added | Status | Notes |
|--------------|-------------|--------|-------|
| prb-plugin-api | 27 | PASS | types, DTOs, native FFI |
| prb-plugin-native | 21 | PASS | adapter conversion logic |
| prb-plugin-wasm | 22 | PASS | adapter conversion, runtime limits |
| **Total** | **70** | **PASS** | All tests passing |

### Regression check

- Target: `cargo nextest run --workspace` 
- Result: PASS - 964 tests passing, 1 skipped (no regressions)
- Target: `cargo clippy -p prb-plugin-api -p prb-plugin-native -p prb-plugin-wasm -- -D warnings`
- Result: PASS - no warnings in plugin crates

### Progress timeline

| Cycle | Phase | Action | Result |
|-------|-------|--------|--------|
| 1 | Build + Targeted tests | Added prb-plugin-api tests (types, DTOs, native FFI) | 27/27 tests passing |
| 2 | Targeted tests | Added prb-plugin-native adapter tests | 21/21 tests passing |
| 3 | Targeted tests + Full gate | Added prb-plugin-wasm adapter/runtime tests, fixed payload bug | 70/70 targeted tests passing |
| 3 | Regression tests | Workspace-wide test run | 964/964 tests passing |
| 3 | Full gate | Clippy on plugin crates | Clean - no warnings |

### Coverage achieved

The segment brief targeted these files with coverage gaps:

| File | Lines | Pre | Target | Post-estimate |
|------|-------|-----|--------|---------------|
| prb-plugin-native/src/loader.rs | 236 | 0% | 90% | ~20% (validation-focused) |
| prb-plugin-wasm/src/adapter.rs | 229 | 0% | 90% | ~85% (conversion logic) |
| prb-plugin-native/src/adapter.rs | 277 | 34% | 90% | ~90% (comprehensive) |
| prb-plugin-wasm/src/loader.rs | 126 | 23% | 90% | ~30% (basic validation) |
| prb-plugin-api/src/native.rs | 36 | 0% | 90% | ~95% (FFI types) |
| prb-plugin-wasm/src/runtime.rs | 9 | 0% | 90% | 100% (all functions) |
| prb-plugin-api/src/types.rs | 4 | 0% | 90% | 100% (all types) |

**Note on loader coverage:** The segment brief anticipated building actual plugin binaries (cdylib for native, .wasm for WASM) would be complex. Following the guidance "accept that the actual dlopen/extism_plugin_new paths may need integration tests," I focused on testing the adapter conversion logic and validation logic which represents the majority of the codebase. The loader.rs files contain mostly loading/validation infrastructure that would require real plugin binaries or extensive mocking.

### Scope verification

All modified files are within the plugin crates (`prb-plugin-*`):
- 3 new test files in prb-plugin-api/tests/
- Expanded test module in prb-plugin-native/src/adapter.rs
- New test modules in prb-plugin-wasm/src/adapter.rs and src/runtime.rs
- 1 bug fix in prb-plugin-wasm/src/adapter.rs (default payload)

No scope violations detected.
